  "description": "Warden Company-Commander of the Lanternfall draft; the PCs' patron.",
  "narrative": "Vael, deed-name earned at Greywake in 995 - she went into the Stilling after her wing-sister and came out alone, torn, carrying the body anyway. Esk commands the Lanternfall draft because no one else would take a dying lane. VOICE: economical, fair, allergic to speeches. She gives the PCs real autonomy and honest accounting. GM USE: patron, not quest dispenser - she tells the company what the Wardens know (including, eventually, the Acceleration Map) and asks what they intend. Her creed passion is the campaign's moral baseline; if the finale demands a price, she volunteers first.",
